ssh user@10.0.0.5
    connects me into max' vm after entering the user password allowing me controll of the system

ssh-keygen
    This command generates the public and private keys for the ssh connections
    By not specifying a name ordirectory for the file it will default to the .ssh folder with the files id_rsa and id_rsa.public

ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub user@10.0.0.5
    This command is used to send the public key to max' system now allowing me to connect without needing the password
